headline: 3 Ways the New U.S. Tariffs Might Affect Amazon Stock
summary: President Donald Trump's "Liberation Day" tariff program set off a string of worries and sent the markets tumbling on Thursday and Friday.  New fears about how the tariffs could trigger a recession sent investors running toward safer instruments like U.S. Treasury bills.  Amazon (NASDAQ: AMZN) stock is one of those stocks and it dropped 12.8% since the tariffs were announced, and it's lost all its gains from the past year.
